{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_0","type":"agent_message","text":"final_filename: p2.cir\n\nObjective: Implement a three-stage NMOS common-source voltage amplifier with one externally driven input node `Vin` and one final output node `Vout`. The circuit should run from `VDD = 5 V` and support `.op` and `.ac dec 20 1 1e9` analyses.\n\nTopology: Use three cascaded common-source stages. Each stage has an NMOS transistor with its source tied to ground, bulk tied to source, drain connected to `VDD` through a resistive load, and gate driven by the previous stage output. Stage 1 gate is driven by `Vin`; stage 3 drain is `Vout`.\n\nRequired devices:\nVDD independent DC supply from node `VDD` to ground, value 5 V.\nInput source connected to exact node `Vin`, using a DC bias of at least 1.2 V and an AC magnitude such as 1 V for small-signal gain measurement.\nThree NMOS transistors using model `NMOS` with W=50u and L=1u:\nM1 drain `n1`, gate `Vin`, source `0`, bulk `0`.\nM2 drain `n2`, gate `n1`, source `0`, bulk `0`.\nM3 drain `Vout`, gate `n2`, source `0`, bulk `0`.\nThree drain load resistors from `VDD` to each drain, each between 10k and 100k ohm. A nominal value such as 47k is suitable:\nR1 from `VDD` to `n1`.\nR2 from `VDD` to `n2`.\nR3 from `VDD` to `Vout`.\n\nBiasing assumptions: `Vin` must be electrically driven by an explicit independent voltage source, not left floating. Use `Vin` DC around 1.5 V to exceed the required NMOS gate bias threshold condition while allowing common-source operation. Intermediate nodes `n1` and `n2` are DC-coupled into the following gates; verify with `.op` that M2 and M3 gate voltages remain high enough for conduction and that all drain nodes avoid rail saturation as much as possible.\n\nAnalyses:\nInclude `.op`.\nInclude `.ac dec 20 1 1e9`.\nInput source should include `AC 1` so voltage gain can be read directly as `V(Vout)/V(Vin)`.\n\nOutput constraints: The final SPICE netlist must contain exact nodes `Vin` and `Vout`. `Vin` must be the circuit input source node. `Vout` must be the drain/output node of the third common-source stage. No subcircuits or placeholder devices should be used."}}
